<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Cache's exception when an illegal id has been used should be better written.
Instead of
Zend_Cache_Exception: Invalid id or tag : must use only [a-zA-Z0-9_]</p>

<p>it would be better to have the illegal id also be written:
Zend_Cache_Exception: Invalid id or tag 'my/false*\TAG' : must use only [a-zA-Z0-9_]</p>

<p>Otherwise it can be very painfull to search which of the 1000nd Cache id's is wrong.
This would improve usability.</p>

